# Since the ".env" file is gitignored, you can use the ".env.example" file to
# build a new ".env" file when you clone the repo. Keep this file up-to-date
# when you add new variables to `.env`.

# This file will be committed to version control, so make sure not to have any
# secrets in it. If you are cloning this repo, create a copy of this file named
# ".env" and populate it with your secrets.

# When adding additional environment variables, the schema in "/src/env.js"
# should be updated accordingly.

# Backend API URLs (optional)
# Recommended: leave these commented out so the browser uses same-origin `/api/*`
# routes and Next.js rewrites/proxying. This avoids CORS/preflight issues.
#
# Only uncomment these when you intentionally want the browser to call backend
# services directly and have already configured CORS for those endpoints.
#
# Default local dev ports used by this project are typically:
# - Gateway: 38001
# - LangGraph: 3024
#
# Direct browser access example (advanced / not recommended by default):
# NEXT_PUBLIC_BACKEND_BASE_URL="http://127.0.0.1:38001"
# NEXT_PUBLIC_LANGGRAPH_BASE_URL="http://127.0.0.1:3024"
